  <div data-q="Do I need a license for an e-bike?" data-a="Most e-bikes don't require a license. Class 1 and 2 e-bikes (up to 20mph) are treated like regular bicycles in most areas. Class 3 e-bikes (up to 28mph) may have additional requirements depending on local laws.">
  
  <div data-q="How long do e-bike batteries last?" data-a="Quality e-bike batteries typically last 3-5 years or 500-1000 charge cycles. Battery life depends on usage, charging habits, and storage conditions. Most batteries retain 80% capacity after 2-3 years of regular use.">
  
  <div data-q="Can I ride an e-bike without pedaling?" data-a="Class 2 e-bikes have throttles that allow riding without pedaling up to 20mph. Class 1 and 3 e-bikes require pedaling to activate the motor assistance. Many riders prefer pedal-assist for exercise and longer range.">
</div>

